cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition systems and language modelling. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with audio data. Additionally, the use of Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) for unsupervised domain discovery suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on acoustic modelling suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing).
